# start Validation Reply Form
_vrf_PLAT480_jin18               
;
PROBLEM: Long H...A H-Bond Reported H2B    ..  I2      ..       3.13 Ang.  
RESPONSE: This distance is actually 2.899 Ang and it's not clear
why there is this discrepancy. In any case, this is just data 
interpretation that does not affect the quality of the refinement.
;
_vrf_PLAT906_jin18               
;
PROBLEM: Large K value in the Analysis of Variance ......      3.133 Check 
RESPONSE: This is likely due to extensive disorder.
;
_vrf_PLAT971_jin18               
;
PROBLEM: Check Calcd Residual Density  0.66A From      I3       1.51 eA-3  
RESPONSE: This peaks is in the vicinity of a heavy element and
is considered noise.
;
_vrf_PLAT977_jin18               
;
PROBLEM: Check the Negative Difference Density on     H1C      -0.48 eA-3  
RESPONSE: There are several alerts of this nature for this refinement,
it has to do with the disorder model.  The refinement is dominated
by the heavy elements that show extensive disorder. 
;
_vrf_PLAT978_jin18               
;
PROBLEM: Number C-C Bonds with Positive Residual Density           0 Note  
RESPONSE: This message does not indicate the structure is deficient. 
With the disorder of the entire structure it is hard to expect an 
ideal behavior.
;
# end Validation Reply Form
